This paper discusses a new intermediate representation (IR) for machine learning frameworks, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper specifically focuses on the challenges of scaling and optimizing machine learning models. The second most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as machine learning is a key component of AI research. The paper also discusses applications of machine learning in computer vision (cs.CV), programming languages (cs.PL), and systems (cs.SY), which are all relevant sub-fields.
